I’ve been here many times, it’s an excellent place for a first date. Huge selection, the wait staff is excellent, and the food is great. If you park in the garage directly across the street, it’s $5 flat rate if you tell them you’re going to Tapas Teatro. About $100 total for a filling dinner for two with a few drinks. I’ll certainly be back!

Very welcoming environment! Sat at the bar and was immediately greeted by the bartender.  Ordered the lamb chops, spinach, shrimp and the flan. Matt (the bartender) helped me choose what house cocktail would be closest to and old fashioned  and nailed it. We discussed the temperature for the lamb chops and I decided to have them cooked medium.  Everything came out perfectly delicious. The best part for me was listening to Matt interact with other guests, he was very knowledgeable of the wines and drinks. But also knowledgeable on various other topics. I myself being from the restaurant industry, can appreciate good service and food. My friend Daz who has been coming to tapas teatro for over 15yrs highly recommended it and took me for a quick bite. Glad that he did! Also Gaby dropped off our food and described them to us, she later walked us to the door and said goodnight before we left. Overall, a very pleasant experience.  I will make the drive from dc and come again.
One of my wife's favorite restaurant. The service is always top notch and food is cooked to perfection.
There is NO BETTER Tapas than this including in Spain where I was 2 weeks ago.  Yo gusto!
I love this place.  I come ever so often but it does get expensive because it takes a lot to get full but it is always worth every bite.
I always enjoy this place. Good drinks, excellent service. A Baltimore gem.

My husband and I went to Tapas Teatro for a Friday evening date night and had such a great experience! The ambiance was calm and smooth, and the service was delightful. That’s not even to mention the food, which struck a perfect balance and mood, and complimented the one before it. Each dish was its own special adventure and eating felt like a warm journey rather than a simple meal. We’ll definitely be going back and seeing what new plates we’ll try next!

I was craving for a Spanish Tortilla for a long time, that’s why we went to Tapas Teatro.  The tortilla was an ok attempt, I was expecting it to be juicer and with more flavor.  The spicy chicken meatballs were really good. Also, the pork chops and the diablas potatoes.  Now, what really caught my attention was my chocolate cake, the ice cream was a home run. One of my friends ordered the cheesecake and it was really good.  Teatro means Theater in English, therefore, I was expecting some kind of Flamenco or Bailo’ show, or at least Spanish music, that did not happen.

Perfect companion to an evening at the movies, Tapas Teatro's location and small plates make it irresistible. This is a small, bustling place with an interior themed to be dark despite a few largely glass doors offering views of the street. As vegetarians who are not fond of goat cheese, we found the menu a bit limited, though we were able to put together a very good meal with our waiter's guidance. Don't miss the baked eggplant with curried vegetables!

I over all really enjoy Tapas Teatro. The service is great, and they keep the olives and bread coming. The only thing keeping it from a "5 star" is that some of the smaller cuts of meat tend to be woefully over done. I had a thin slice of salmon about a 1/2 a centimeter thick and it was like jerky. I had a similar experience with Chicken. All of the MANY other items I had were delicious.

Tapas Teatro is a cute tapas restaurant next to the Charles theater, hence "Tapas Teatro." The dining area is cramped, and it's hard to move around without bumping into another chair, patron or server. There is usually a line, but it moves quickly, and we were able to get to our movie on time.  The first time I dined there with my husband, the waiter was upbeat, and encouraging without being pushy. He kept an eye on us the whole time, and when we were getting close to finishing our plates, we had another plate on our table in no time. It felt like we had spent $100, but when we received our check, we were relieved that the tab was closer to $50.  The second time we were there, the server wasn't as attentive, and when we finished our food we had to flag down our server, and our experience that day was disappointing.  The tapas are sized for what you'd expect for tapas, and the plates are seasoned well. There were some dishes we liked more than others, but we never got a plate we didn't like.

This was a lovely place to get a bite to eat. They have a good selection of cocktails. The tapas are delicious. I would recommend getting a few to share. There were three of us and we shared 5 different dishes. They were perfect. The dessert selection was small but what we ordered was good.  The service was a little on the slow side but we weren't in a hurry so that was ok.
The food was absolutly great, service also.
Gernerally very good food and service

What a wonderful surprise! We ended up in Baltimore for dinner by accident. Downtown on a Friday was packed - waits over two hours. So we headed up to the fab new Station North and this wonderful tapas place. Service was extraordinary thanks to Seth, who encouraged us to take our time and try things a few at a time. Highlights, besides everything: perfectly grilled calamari, wonderful little chorizos, chévere cheesecake (OMG). The Sangria was the real deal - fruit soaked in wine and not watered down with too much ice. The dipping oil for the bread was made with fresh roasted garlic. Yum. We will be back!  The place is lovely. We sat a sidewalk table right by the Charles movie theater where we could watch the evening unfold while we relaxed with our wonderful food.
I absolutely love this place! The ambiance and the food are great.  You've got to try their croquetas de pollo. They have a nice wine selection and yummy cocktails too!

I wish I could say that the food was good enough for me to return, but the service I experienced was enough to keep me away for good. This is a great place for Spanish food. Everything was incredibly flavorful. Portions are generous by tapas standards. The Manchego cheese and pomegranate onion sauce was not a flavor combination I would think would go together but it was amazing. The Catalan kale and pisto Manchego were very flavorful and perfectly cooked. The papas cambray were a bit undercooked and not what I expected, but anything else I would highly recommend. There is a parking lot nearby but you have to pay for it. I would take the light rail to the University of Baltimore stop and walk 5 minutes. It's a pretty safe area by Baltimore standards.

Visiting Baltimore for first time. Great atmosphere and location, however everything fell short from there. Their Gin drinks were good but Jameson and Gingerale was off. As far as the food, the Jamon Serrano was too dry and definitely not fresh. The steak was chewy and fatty. Great Food,Great service, great place my only complaint is that a found shattered glass inside my dessert, they were very apologetic about it, sorry for the bad review, i absolutely loved the place  but the fact that i almost swallowed a piece of glass and probably die, disturbs me...  well i guess they were cool enough to not include that dessert in my check ... and again they were very sorry about it. no bad feelings guys.

Great place for tapas.  Awesome service at the bar.

Finally, I was able to find time to come here! Believe it or not, for a Saturday night it was pretty slow (thank God). We were sat down immediately and we were not rushed at all.  The food is plentiful (5 small tapas filled 2 of us), we barely finished it though. Everything was full of flavor and made us smile after every bite! We can't wait to go back!  The only reason I'm taking 1 star off of it is because I wasn't too impressed with the olive oil used for dipping of the bread...kind of tasted like a Trader Joes brand, regardless it was still tasty. We also weren't a big fan of whatever they put inside the olive oil, something fruity (I may be wrong)...  Regardless, probably the best Tapas place around Baltimore.

This is a slightly unorthodox Spanish cuisine. Most of the classics are available on the menu with some variation from what I usually find in Spanish restaurants. The quality of the food was quite good. As with any tapas restaurant, there are some things on the menu they do amazingly well and others that I'd rather eat somewhere else. I found a couple things I really enjoyed and had a great meal.  The service was quite good. The server was attentive and I always had what I needed. It can get quite busy, but our table was never neglected and the host did a great job of seating our large party in a timely fashion.  The price was typical, if slightly higher, for a tapas restaurant.
This place has the best selections of food, sangria and I cannot say enough about the honey drizzled fried manchego cheese dish. It is a MUST visit place in Baltimore

I have been a loyal regular for many years.  Unfortunately my past two visits I was treated disrespectfully.  Even guests around me we talking about my treatment.  I spoke with Helmand who knows me being as though I am a regular.  Yet no real surprise, apology, or anything much followed.  I did give it another try but also was disrespected and I spoke with long time waiter, who also offered no real help.  I feel as though my years of loyal patronage means nothing.

Food was downright fantastic.  Best Chile Rellenos I've ever had by far.  $10 for a pitcher of excellent sangria (was enough for about 3 smallish glasses each for 3 people).  Our waitress was very friendly and checked on us at good intervals.  We were never left wondering where she was and when she was coming back.  It was a little cramped at the 3 person table (with only 3 of us) and it was louder than I like, but not awful.  I took off from decor for these, because there is no "atmosphere" field.  The actual decor was nice, minimal, and subdued.  Nothing flashy to distract you, but not bland/boring either.

Food-wise, extremely well done. I am married to a Spanish girl, and having been to Spain myself, the paella was as close as it gets to traditional Spain. The tapas we ordered were good too. On the other hand, the waitress was extremely rude. We are a young couple and I think she pegged us for poor tippers. She didn't ask how our food was once and rolled her eyes when we asked her to box something up. She did say thank you when she gave us the check, like someone was forcing her with a gun to her head. Besides this factor, everything else was great. Bottom line - go there for good food, avoid pudgy blonde waitress.
